## Disclaimer

This repository is a **simplified and fully reproducible demonstration** of a methodology used to construct a composite index of public service quality.

All datasets included in this repository are **simulated data created solely for educational and methodological purposes**. No confidential or administrative data from ANStat, OSEP, or any public institution are used.

The views expressed in this repository are **strictly personal and academic** and do not represent the official position of ANStat, OSEP, or any governmental institution.

This repository aims to illustrate a **transparent and reproducible statistical pipeline** for building a composite public service quality index.


## Code Structure – INQSP Methodology Demo

This folder contains the **complete Stata pipeline** used to compute a simplified and reproducible version of the **Public Service Quality Index (INQSP)**.

The pipeline follows a structured approach based on:

- dimension construction
- indicator aggregation
- composite index computation

All scripts rely on **relative paths** defined in `00_setup.do`, ensuring full portability across operating systems and users.


## File Structure

### 00_setup.do

Environment initialization script.

This file:

- defines global paths (`DATA`, `OUT`, `CODE`)
- ensures Stata is launched from the project root
- prepares the working environment for the analysis

This script must always be executed before running analytical scripts.


### 00_master.do

Master execution script.

This file:

- calls `00_setup.do`
- executes all analytical scripts in the correct order
- reproduces the complete INQSP pipeline

Recommended entry point for full replication:

`do code/00_master.do`


### 01_quality_transformation.do

Computes **Dimension 1 – Quality of Public Service Transformation Initiatives**

Sub-indices:

- Sub-index 1: Existence of operational mechanisms
- Sub-index 2: Appropriation of the “Fonctionnaire Nouveau” concept

The dimension score is calculated using **equal weighting**.


### 02_quality_services_received.do

Computes **Dimension 2 – Quality of Services Received**

Sub-indices include:

- Assessment of service quality by civil society organizations
- Assessment of service quality by users

Indicators are aggregated to produce a composite score for service reception quality.


### 03_quality_services_delivered.do

Computes **Dimension 3 – Quality of Services Delivered by Public Service Delivery Points (PPSP)**

This dimension is constructed using five sub-indices:

- Working conditions of frontline staff
- Physical work environment and resources
- Information provided to users
- Service continuity mechanisms
- Staff–user interactions

Each sub-index is aggregated using a **simple average**.


### 04_quality_services_by_dm.do

Computes **Dimension 4 – Perception of Public Service Quality by Decision-Makers**

Indicators include:

- Overall satisfaction
- Observed changes in service delivery
- Absence of structural challenges
- Existence of monitoring mechanisms

The dimension score is computed as a **simple composite index**.


### 05_final_index.do

Final aggregation script.

This script:

- imports dimension scores from previous outputs
- computes the **National Public Service Quality Index (INQSP)**
- exports the consolidated results table to Excel.


## Pipeline Overview

The INQSP pipeline follows the structure:

Dimension 1 – Transformation initiatives  
Dimension 2 – Quality of services received  
Dimension 3 – Quality of services delivered  
Dimension 4 – Decision-makers perception  
↓  
National Composite Index (INQSP)

The final index is computed as:

INQSP = (D1 + D2 + D3 + D4) / 4

All dimensions receive **equal weights**.


## Technical Requirements

- Stata 17 or higher
- No external Stata packages required
- The code relies exclusively on built-in Stata commands


## Reproducibility

To reproduce the full pipeline:

`do code/00_master.do`

All results will be automatically generated in the **OUT** folder.
